<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="postbody">I am assuming M1 = Vxed. 
<br />
 
<br />
In that case, this is not new. I believe the easy availability of blue con (to a 65) Pooka, the preferred non-summoning charm pet was nerfed in one of the earlier "revamps" of GoD. Where it used to be almost all pookas were charmable in the early days of GoD; these days you'd be lucky to find one at the beginning the trial near the ZI, where most of the killings occur. Thats why if you find one, its good to take care of the pet. It also makes it tough for the soloing Vxed chanter... It doesn't stop soloing druids or necros tho. 
<br />
 
<br />
OTH, if you are not fussy over pet selection, try using a Hynid (doggy antelope?) or a Cragbeast (giant lizard). They don't summon but they do proc  (resistable) stuns when they break. They are also a lot more plentiful here and in Tipt. Avoid stonemites at all cost, they summon, hit hard and proc a nasty poison. 
<br />
 
<br />
If M1 &lt;&gt; Vxed, then never mind. 
<br />
<img src="images/smiles/icon_rolleyes.gif" alt="icon_rolleyes.gif" border="0" /></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
</td></tr>
